# Is Subsequence (Two Pointers) - SCN Notes

## Concept

A string `s` is a subsequence of `t` if all characters of `s` appear in `t` in the same order, not necessarily consecutively.

Use two pointers:

* `i` → traverses `s`
* `j` → traverses `t`

Whenever characters match, move both pointers. Otherwise, move only `j`.

---

## Approach

### 1. Handle Empty String

An empty string is always a subsequence.

```java
if(s.length() == 0)
{
    return true;
}
```

---

### 2. Traverse Both Strings

If characters match:

```java
if(s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j))
{
    i++;
    j++;
}
```

Otherwise:

```java
j++;
```

Continue until either string is exhausted.

---

### 3. Check Result

If all characters of `s` are matched:

```java
i == s.length()
```

Then `s` is a subsequence of `t`.

---

## Code

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isSubsequence(String s, String t) {
        if(s.length() == 0)
        {
            return true;
        }

        int i = 0;
        int j = 0;

        while(i < s.length() && j < t.length())
        {
            if(s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j))
            {
                i++;
                j++;
            }
            else
            {
                j++;
            }
        }

        if(i < s.length())
        {
            return false;
        }
        else
        {
            return true;
        }
    }
}
```

---

## Key Points

* Maintain the order of characters.
* Characters do not need to be contiguous.
* Move pointer `i` only when a match is found.
* Move pointer `j` in every iteration.
* If all characters of `s` are matched, return `true`.

---

## Complexity

```java
Time  : O(n)
Space : O(1)
```

where:

```java
n = t.length()
```

